## 5. ADMIN PANEL RULES
- Admin route: /admin (protected by JWT cookie 'admin_token')
- Login route: /admin/login
- All admin DB writes go through: direct Supabase client calls from the admin client component (authorized via JWT middleware protecting /admin/*)
- Error handling: EVERY Supabase operation must check for error and call showToast(error.message, 'error') on failure.
- Settings save flow: Admin → saveSettings({banner, site}) → POST /api/admin/settings → supabase.upsert({key:'site', value: siteSettings}) + supabase.upsert({key:'banner', value: banner}) → revalidatePath('/').
- Banner display: PromoBanner component reads from useSiteSettings() context (SSR-loaded). Banner changes appear after page refresh (not real-time in admin preview).

## 6. LEAD PIPELINE RULES
- Flow: DB insert (leads table) → Puppeteer PDF → Telegram notification → Email copy.
- Fallback: If PDF fails, Telegram must still fire. If Email fails, lead must still be in DB.
- PDF: uses Puppeteer (server-side HTML template). Cyrillic supported via HTML/CSS (no jsPDF).
- Telegram: send via BOT_TOKEN + ADMIN_CHAT_ID env vars. Bot token format: 123456:ABCdef...
- Email: SMTP via env vars (SMTP_HOST, SMTP_PORT, SMTP_USER, SMTP_PASS, ADMIN_EMAIL).

## 7. CODE QUALITY RULES
- TypeScript strict mode. No 'any'. No implicit type assertions without justification.
- No dead/commented code. No console.log in production paths (use console.error/warn for real errors only).
- Tailwind CSS only — no inline styles except for dynamic values. No CSS modules.
- Framer Motion for all animations. Use whileInView with viewport={{ once: true }} for scroll animations.
- Images: always use next/image with proper fill + sizes props. Never use raw <img> for product/portfolio images.
- Before reporting a bug fixed, verify by re-reading the changed file and tracing the data flow mentally.

